text:
we are ready to support @verahouseinc and hope you are too! orders must be placed before feb 28th and i plan to ship or schedule pick up by mid-march. i do not carry inventory so this gives two weeks for production. go to kkdiscovers.com to place order and read story behind the #stronger project! üíúnote the reason behind the colors selected for apparel: 
purple is the color to represent domestic violence, however, the meaning behind selecting  purple, white and gold goes back even further. the women's suffrage movement utilized purple, white and gold in the early 1900's and were the colors of the national women's party. the colors started over in england and symbolized purity, hope and loyalty. k.k. discovers wants to bring important history to the forefront while bringing awareness to the mission of vera house!üíú #kkdiscovers #projectlove #apparel #hats #giveback #onelove #enddomesticviolence #metoo #verahouse #domesticviolence #womenempowerment #support #sexualassault

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i know how to do this, on the surface... how to do more, how to do too much, how to overdo it, how to fall prey to the cult of busyness and productivity porn and overachieving for everyone's benefit except my own. oh, how i know. right now, though, the thing i must do (the thing i cannot do, the thing i cannot get myself to do) is give myself a break. slow it down. stop. rest. i know this trap all too well; it's been a year since fibromyalgia stepped out of the shadows where it had been lurking, content to be ignored and chalked up to [fill in the excuses i made for the pain, the crushing fatigue]. i'm in the middle of another year of now-common q1 work insanity, travel, buried under way too many responsibilities with far too few resources. my body isn't going to let me get through this week's trip unscathed - hell, i haven't even (re)packed yet and i'm feral with pain, fetal-position exhausted. the thing i must do is still the thing i cannot do. and it's going to catch up with me. if i'm being honest, it already has.
@thewordforthis

text:
i wouldn‚Äôt stop fighting them,
twisting in bed, falling to the floor, until
they hoisted me up and
held me down,
with four hands,
twenty fingers,
and pillows‚Äî
a fuck ton of pillows.
it wasn‚Äôt the red wine that did it,
it wasn‚Äôt the mugs of glogg,
it wasn‚Äôt the six shots of bourbon
after all.
it wasn‚Äôt the empty stomach,
it wasn‚Äôt the dancing,
it wasn‚Äôt the cut off sign at the bar.
no, that‚Äôs not what started this all.
i couldn‚Äôt stop sobbing.
tears jumping into the cold bed
beneath me.
overflowing;
only getting worse as i said,
‚Äúdon‚Äôt leave, don‚Äôt leave me alone.‚Äù
‚Äúi thought he loved me.‚Äù
‚Äúdon‚Äôt leave me.‚Äù
‚Äúhe raped me.‚Äù
‚Äúi thought he loved me; he raped me.‚Äù
‚Äúhe...he...i thought he‚Äîdon‚Äôt leave me alone. please.‚Äù
‚Äúplease.‚Äù
‚Äúplease...‚Äù
they told me he was no longer here,
no longer in my home.
they reassured me i was safe,
repeating it over and over
and over.
‚Äúyou‚Äôre safe now.‚Äù
‚Äúhe‚Äôs not here anymore, he‚Äôs gone.‚Äù
‚Äúthe locks are changed.‚Äù
‚Äúyou‚Äôre safe, lj.‚Äù
releasing their grasp,
brushing my hair back,
placing the rubbish bin beside my bed.
but still i begged,
‚Äúdon‚Äôt leave me alone.‚Äù
this was the night
i hit my low.
the bottom
of wine,
of bourbon,
of anything to numb the pain.
‚Äúhe raped me,‚Äù i whispered.
again, even after they left.
still in disbelief,
still pretending
my entire life hadn‚Äôt changed.
.
.
.

.
üíôüíôi hope you know you‚Äôre not alone. that even at your lowest, the ground will have your back. healing is a painful journey but it‚Äôs worth it and one day, you will smile, if not again then perhaps for the first time. üíôüíô
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

.
if you are under the age of 35 and are thinking of buying a home, then you are already surpassing your peers.

text_retweet:
#repost @tedxpenn with @make_repost
„Éª„Éª„Éª
closing the gender gap üîé

with the recent rise of the #metoo movement, there has been increasingly more conversation about sexism in the workplace. in light of such events, companies have instituted "diversity training" to bring awareness to gender issues and resolve discrimination.

however, research has found that corporate ‚Äúdiversity training‚Äù actually makes the gender gap worse, partly because it makes men feel demonized. however unintended, such training divides men and women on a crucial problem that requires a coordinated effort to address.

the growing disconnect between men and women stems from a lack of effective communication. while women tend to discuss these issues amongst themselves, men are often unexposed to such conversations. as a result, despite their good intentions, men are often left wondering how they should support women and what they should say (and not say). this uncertainty in how to behave can lead to missteps, frustration, and misunderstandings that can result in real and lasting damage on women‚Äôs careers.

joanne lipman, author of "that's what she said", advocates that the best way to bridge the gender gap is by bringing men into the conversation of sexism. as someone who has worked her way to the top of a male-dominated industry, she has a unique perspective on how we can achieve workplace parity and why men must be mobilized to help close the gender gap.

as one of the nation's leading journalists, joanne has served as chief content officer of gannett and editor-in-chief of usa today and the usa today network. under her leadership, the usa today network received three pulitzer prizes, including the first pulitzer in usa today's history.

she will be speaking at our 2019 tedxpenn conference, where you can hear about her strategies and solutions to break down the gender barrier and her roadmap to empowering women as true equals.
-
#tedxpenn #tedxtalks #tedx #sexism #genderequality #gendergap #diversitytraining #empoweringwomen #philadelphia

text:
emotional self-harm: what i have come to identify and label in myself today. all day i‚Äôve been excessively self-critical and feeling especially out of my depth. i have been lacklustrous and resentful of myself despite trying to behave normally. i have been damaging my self-esteem - or it has been damaging me. it‚Äôs difficult to make conversation when you feel incapable, inadequate and insignificant. when you envisage other people and how they fare better than you. when you anticipate that people consider you not cut out for this. when you dread their disappointment in you. but i cannot muster up the energy or courage to do anything about it... because i feel so low. it has hit me hard because it has hit me fast and i don‚Äôt know what else to do except sleep and reassess in the morning. ~copingdiary

text:
let me tell ya somethin‚Äô i discovered last year and keeps surprising me and i continue to work on because i didn‚Äôt understand before... communication.

specially with family and relatives is difficult for me, as a kid my parents would spend hours trying to get me to talk but i was too afraid to speak up because when i would my mom would overpower my words and i‚Äôd be made fun of. so over the years i stopped talking. i started keeping everything bottled up, in my marriage i did the same thing because it‚Äôs all i had learned to do. it got to the point where i had panic/anxiety attack after panic/anxiety attack. the moment i acknowledged that my words and feelings matter i began to speak up and stand up for myself. to this day i have challenges when it comes to speaking. if yall watched any of my lives in the past two weeks with @theselflovewitch @synergysoul_ and @solaristhehiipriestess it‚Äôs noticeable i still have difficulty expressing my words. i lived 23+ years keeping everything bottled up. that shit gets to you and it‚Äôs really damaging on all levels. even my physical body still suffers from that.

i am forever grateful for my love because he is the first person that ever encouraged me and made me feel safe to be able to speak up about anything and everything. 
my mom, i don‚Äôt blame her for any of my traumas because it was all a chain, generations and generations of miscommunication and bottled up feelings and suffering.

and this is where it ends.

while i heal myself, i heal my mother, my grandmother and the women before her.

while i heal my wounds, i protect my daughters and the daughters to come from the same wounds.

communicate what you need, express yourself, talk, stop sending hints and expecting others to understand you. speak up.
name: The Stoner Goddess
tweet_full:
let me tell ya somethin‚Äô i discovered last year and keeps surprising me and i continue to work on because i didn‚Äôt understand before... communication.

specially with family and relatives is difficult for me, as a kid my parents would spend hours trying to get me to talk but i was too afraid to speak up because when i would my mom would overpower my words and i‚Äôd be made fun of. so over the years i stopped talking. i started keeping everything bottled up, in my marriage i did the same thing because it‚Äôs all i had learned to do. it got to the point where i had panic/anxiety attack after panic/anxiety attack. the moment i acknowledged that my words and feelings matter i began to speak up and stand up for myself. to this day i have challenges when it comes to speaking. if yall watched any of my lives in the past two weeks with @theselflovewitch @synergysoul_ and @solaristhehiipriestess it‚Äôs noticeable i still have difficulty expressing my words. i lived 23+ years keeping everything bottled up. that shit gets to you and it‚Äôs really damaging on all levels. even my physical body still suffers from that.

i am forever grateful for my love because he is the first person that ever encouraged me and made me feel safe to be able to speak up about anything and everything. 
my mom, i don‚Äôt blame her for any of my traumas because it was all a chain, generations and generations of miscommunication and bottled up feelings and suffering.

and this is where it ends.

while i heal myself, i heal my mother, my grandmother and the women before her.

while i heal my wounds, i protect my daughters and the daughters to come from the same wounds.

communicate what you need, express yourself, talk, stop sending hints and expecting others to understand you. speak up.

working out, how come some days we can push ourselves to exhaustion and other days we‚Äôre praying to god to help us not pass out? and do you recognize the difference? i love the days when i can push myself to exhaustion!
.
there‚Äôs different factors that play into why we may feel one way or another, right? but i want to talk about food! #foodisfuel
.
bottom line, our bodies need carbohydrates! they give us energy!
.
i‚Äôm learning that i need 50-60 grams of carbohydrates before i lift weights to really be able to give it my all. üèãüèº‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
.
to be clear, this doesn‚Äôt mean my workouts are all of a sudden easy. that‚Äôs not the point. but there is a huge difference between feeling light headed & nauseous ü§¢ versus being able to push myself to exhaustion. üí™üèº
.
are you heading out for a workout? don‚Äôt forget your fuel. need a good option? make this rice pudding and pair it with some fruit and you‚Äôll be set!
.
also, saved in my highlights are some of my pre-weights meals. i‚Äôll keep adding to it so check it out if want some ideas! üí°
.
oven baked rice pudding
- 2 cups cooked brown rice
- 2 cups almond milk
- 2 eggs
- 5 tbsp. maple syrup
- 1 tsp. vanilla
- 1 tsp. cinnamon
.
pour rice in the bottom of an 8x8 baking dish. mix all other ingredients together and pour over the top. bake at 350 for an hour and 15 minutes.
.

text:
'am i required to provide harassment training' and other faqs

q: am i required to provide sexual harassment training?
a: several states and local jurisdictions require employers to provide sexual harassment training. your state may also have industry-specific requirements. for example, california has additional requirements for employees who provide janitorial services. even if you aren't required to provide sexual harassment training, it is a best practice to do so.

q: are all employees required to receive sexual harassment training?
a: it varies by jurisdiction. here are some general guidelines for who is covered by training requirements in each jurisdiction.

q: what must be covered in harassment training?
a: these laws typically have very specific requirements for the content of the training.

q: can i just play a video to comply with these laws?
a: the laws typically require that, at a minimum, training be interactive. a program that requires an employee to watch a training video, with no feedback mechanism or interaction, generally wouldn't be considered interactive under these laws.

q: who can lead the training?
a: your law may require that trainers meet certain standards. for example, california requires trainers to be one or more of the following:
attorneys admitted to the bar for two or more years whose practice includes state and federal nondiscrimination laws; or
human resource professionals or harassment prevention consultants with a minimum of two years of practical experience; or
professors or instructors who have either 20 instruction hours or two or more years of experience in a law school or college teaching about state and federal nondiscrimination laws.

a: several states and local jurisdictions require employers to provide sexual harassment training. your state may also have industry-specific requirements. for example, california has additional requirements for employees who provide janitorial services. even if you are not required to provide sexual harassment training, it is a best practice to do so.

q: are all employees required to receive sexual harassment training?
a: it varies by jurisdiction. here are some general guidelines for who is covered by training requirements in each jurisdiction.

q: what must be covered in harassment training?
a: these laws typically have very specific requirements for the content of the training.

q: can i just play a video to comply with these laws?
a: the laws typically require that, at a minimum, training be interactive. a program that requires an employee to watch a training video, with no feedback mechanism or interaction, generally would not be considered interactive under these laws.

q: who can lead the training?
a: your law may require that trainers meet ceain standards. for example, california requires trainers to be one or more of the following:
attorneys admitted to the bar for two or more years whose practice includes state and federal nondiscrimination laws; or
human resource professionals or harassment prevention consultants with a minimum of two years of practical experience; or
professors or instructors who have either 20 instruction hours or two or more years of experience in a law school or college teaching about state and federal nondiscrimination laws.

text:
newest article went up a few days ago. when i started on my evangel journey, i never could have imagined making any kind of impact. i thought, "just show up, get stuff done, ans graduate." but college challenges you in ways you never thought and you develop passions you never thought you would have had. that's what happened for me since stepping onto this campus. when the article first went live, i was scared to death. i was wondering if i did the right thing. then, messages began to pour in; messages from girls, some i knew and some i didn't, who experienced this same thing on campus. girls who felt voiceless during their time here. i just can't believe i was even able to play a part in that. 
the love i hold for my university is very real. i've made life long friends, i've found things i'm passionate about, i've had incredible professors, and i've grown in ways i never would have expected. something i've learned is that you can still love something and desire change. it doesn't have to be a this or that thing. 
i understand the article might have stirred up emotions and questions, and i just want you to know that i am here. i am here if you just need someone to listen and i am here if gou want to ask questions or start discussions around this topic. 
#sexualassaultawareness #odysseyonline #article #linkinbio #odysseycommunity #odysseycreator #mycampustoo #metoo

why are #metoo accused getting a pass in kidlit? üìöaccusations against @drewdaywalt: ‚Äúanother writer says, ‚Äúduring an award ceremony during a conference in los angeles, i thought how lucky i was to sit next to a huge bestseller in the children‚Äôs industry. our entire table enjoyed dinner together and near the end he expressed how he‚Äôd be interested in reading my work and give feedback. as a newer writer, this was a dream and we exchanged cards. after that, i started to receive messages from him about how beautiful my social media pictures were and that we should get together sometime. he then proceeded to tell me that his wife was fine with it, as she dates other people too. when i told him i was married and declined, he then got upset and pretended to never have met me.‚Äù for this writer, ‚Äúhe made me never want to go back to los angeles. this happened years ago, and he made me feel like an object, not a professional.‚Äù üìö accusation 1: ‚Äúmy story was also mentioned in anne‚Äôs article, and drew daywalt was the one that made me never want to return to los angeles. this is really tough for me to post, even anonymously, because i‚Äôve always tried to be such a peacemaker, but honestly, the more i thought about it, the more i realized that this goes beyond me. i felt confused and hurt over the entire interaction for a long while, and after reading anne‚Äôs response in her article, she truly helped me understand why i felt the way i did. thank you, anne! and to those also speaking up, i‚Äôm glad we‚Äôre all having this conversation, and my hope is that those being called out will truly reach out for help and want to change. ‚Äù

accusation 2 (via twitter dm to me): ‚Äúhello, i was recently told about your blog post featuring comments about men in the kid lit community who are accused of sexually harassing women. when i read anne ursu‚Äôs article, i knew exactly who one of the men were. drew daywalt. he used the same lines with me and more. i am forever traumatized by that man. i wish to remain anonymous.‚Äù üìömy post here: https://www.pragmaticmom.com/2019/01/why-are-metoo-accused-getting-a-pass-in-kidlit/ #drewdaywalt #sexualmisconduct #picture

text:
a non veggie dinner! frozen fish fillets defrosted and then coated in egg and breadcrumbs with celeriac chips (which the kids get mega excited for) and just boiled veg as sometimes that is quite nice! 
was a happy meal to end a happy day. started off with a good swim-50 lengths in 30 mins so def getting faster.
i then met the police officer who has dealt with my case for the past two years. this woman is incredible. she has reassured me, comforted me, strengthened me and just been totally amazing at her job and always gone that bit further to make sure i was comfortable. she is the first person i ever spoke to about the details of what happened to me and she managed to help get me to a point of being able to stand in court and stand up for myself. she believed in me and helped me find my voice and speak out. it was so lovely to be able to see her and show her how much better i am doing. it was quite bittersweet saying thank you and goodbye as i genuinely liked her but am so very happy this part of my life has been closed. 
#pescatarian #healthylifestyle
#healthykidsfood #dinnerrecipes #homemade #swimming #swimathon2019 #training #police #ukpolice #speak #metoo #silencekills #strength #support #kindness #newlife #newbeginnings #timeforchange #movingon

text:
we have a design that proclaims ‚Äúpatriarchy is fitna,‚Äù yet some folks have a hard time understanding what this means in real life.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..
as a group of professional muslims working with heart, we could probably publish a few volumes of books about how we‚Äôve come across and dealt with patriarchy in our professional and personal spaces.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..
what many folks continue to not understand is that patriarchy exists because of gender inequity, power and control, and rape culture. and that these all contribute to abuse and violence.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.
in this case, religion was used to gain the upper hand in the conversation. mix in some male privilege, since the spiritual leader was speaking to someone who identifies as female, and you‚Äôve got patriarchy in practice.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.
we know that we‚Äôre not alone with experiencing this. and we‚Äôre hopeful that someday, patriarchy will cease to exist.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.
but this is what we need to keep chipping away at. by calling it out. by pushing back. and by refusing to compromise our values to acquiesce to patriarchy.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..

text: ‚Äúshe lied to the media, she lied to the victims, she lied to congress,‚Äù assistant attorney general scott teter said about ex-msu president lou anna simon during her preliminary hearing at the eaton county courthouse in charlotte, michigan, on tuesday, feb. 5, 2019. simon is accused of lying to police about her knowledge of a 2014 incident involving larry nassar's abuse of a patient at the msu sports medicine clinic. she faces two felony and two misdemeanor counts of lying to a peace officer. nassar pleaded guilty in 2018 for molesting hundreds of patients over two decades under the guise of medical treatment while he served as a sports-medicine doctor for michigan state university and the u.s. national gymnastics team. (richard shotwell/invision/ap) pasadena, calif. ‚Äî when the louis c.k. scandal detonated in late 2017 and fx severed its considerable ties to the ¬≠comedian-producer, fans of ‚Äúbetter things‚Äù worried about the fate of their favorite show, which c.k. co-created and co-wrote with its star, pamela adlon. rather than fall into a trap of becoming a designated female interpreter of c.k.‚Äôs feelings ‚Äî after he admitted to several acts of sexual misconduct against women ‚Äî adlon broke off the friendship (as recounted in a long profile appearing in the latest issue of the new yorker) and doubled down on her show. let‚Äôs be honest, she deserved most of the credit for it all along. with support from fx and four new writers, adlon spent more than a year making the 12 episodes in the third season of ‚Äúbetter things‚Äù(premiering feb. 28), all of which she also directed. as adlon explained monday at the television critics association‚Äôs winter press tour, she focused on what she could control, which is the tone and working environment of her own hollywood set. it paid off. of‚Ä¶

text:
hacienda nurse accused of raping vegetative woman | we want local news ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
https://wewantlocal.com/news/‚†Ä
‚†Ä
an arizona nurse pleaded not guilty on tuesday to raping a severely disabled woman, a crime that came to light when the victim unexpectedly gave birth in the long-term care facility where she has a patient for about two decades.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
nathan sutherland, 36, wearing an orange jumpsuit and shackled at the wrists and legs, entered his plea at a brief arraignment hearing at the maricopa county superior court. his next court appearance was set for march 19.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
sutherland, a licensed practical nurse who began working at hacienda healthcare skilled nursing facility in phoenix in 2012, faces one count each of sexual assault and abuse of a vulnerable adult. he has been held on $500,000 bail since last month.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
police arrested sutherland last month after investigators linked him to the case through dna evidence after the woman, who is in her 20s, went into labor on dec. 29 at hacienda healthcare.‚†Ä
‚†Ä

meet our founder!!!
tyde-couney edwards is the founding director of ballet after dark. she's also a classically trained ballerina, choreographer, a model and survivor of sexual assault. born and raised in baltimore city, she is a graduate of the baltimore school for the as and has over 20 years of dance training and experience. trained in various styles of dance including classical and contemporary ballet, pointe, modern, lyrical, jazz, tap and hip-hop, she conceptualized ballet after dark after struggling with recovery following her sexual assault. tyde-couney has trained with debbie allen dance academy, dance theatre of harlem, peabody conservatory, joffrey ballet, alvin ailey and other institutions while receiving training from local dance pioneers such as anton wilson, norma pera and stephanie powell. she currently resides in baltimore city.

text:
do you know that many children being sexually abused do not understand that what is happening to them is wrong or that it is considered abuse let alone that it is a crime?
‚ú®
i used to think children didn‚Äôt come forward because they were being threatened. that certainly does happen, but i‚Äôve read so many survivor stories that are like sarah‚Äôs story where the realization of what happened to them comes when they are older. many describe the realization coming while having a normal conversation with a friend or, like sarah, a counselor and suddenly everything starts to fall in place and make sense.
‚ú®
i‚Äôve learned that there are many reasons this might happen, but one of the main reasons is that predators are very skilled at embedding the abuse inside ‚Äúnormal‚Äù activities. predators are also very skilled at using shame, guilt, fear, and even ‚Äúlove‚Äù to confuse and silence a child.
‚ú®
understanding this is critically important to believe, protect, and defend the child. please don't ask, "how could they not have known?" instead ask, "how did the abuser do this?" keep the child at the center of your support and the focus on what the abuser did.
‚ú®

i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
the good ol‚Äô you never know what happens behind closed doors. i mean let‚Äôs face it, we were fooled by them initially. so how couldn‚Äôt people be fooled by them when they don‚Äôt know them like we do? sure, sometimes the mask falls in certain situations‚Äîlike the time my husband was drunk and wanted to go through the in n out drive thru and proceeded to act like a complete asshat to the poor guy standing outside taking our order. i was 4 months pregnant with our first, so sober as hell and embarrassed as hell. my husband was acting manic: saying something rude, then his evil, loud and obnoxious laugh would follow, then he‚Äôd snap at me for something with those darkened eyes and then he‚Äôd start laughing again. he poked fun at me and joked all the way home, then i walked into the front door without waiting for him and next thing i knew i was being grabbed around my neck and pulled backwards down to the floor. he had just been laughing (although at my expense)...so what prompted the violence? that up and down and sideways and back down again...that‚Äôs the kind of shit we live with, but people don‚Äôt see. how can you be mad at yourself for loving this amazing person you fell in love with? that person was amazing!! but they also never existed. ‚Ä¢

text:
#theanonletters
speaking up could save countless others.
-
the anon letters is a project created to encourage survivors to reach out. it aims to give you a safe space to share their experiences, ask for advice from others through our page, or give advice about your journey towards healing that you think other survivors should hear. you are able to choose whether you want it to be shared on our page or not. your identity remains anonymous. the link to the google form is in our bio.

text: this picture is from end of summer, september or so. i just cut my hair off and this was just soooo freeing ! feeling the wind on my scalp üòç do you know this freeling ? now i‚Äôm used to it and i guess it‚Äôs like everything: you get used to it. in some cases it‚Äôs fine, it‚Äôs actually good to get used to something. like i‚Äôd love to get used to going to the gym but no... doesn‚Äôt work. but i feel like sometimes i get used to things i shouldn‚Äôt get used to. like talking about #igm or the discriminations i, as an intersex woman or #intersex in general face. of course i m angry and i want it to change, but it kind of got normal, i‚Äôve got my story, my facts, my arguments ready. and anyway, in this world a hit happens... at a time i even got used to thinking i was alone and i would never meet someone like me... i got used to my hidden body and shameful existence that i almost forgot about it. i don‚Äôt really know if this post makes sense but i‚Äôm coming home from work and been thinking about this so... like there‚Äôs so much injustice everywhere and it almost doesn‚Äôt make us feel sad/angry/revolted anymore... you are used to seeing migrants drown in the see, you are used to seeing old men run our governments, companies and society, until #metoo we were used to being verbally or physically abused, we forgot this was actually not ok. but i don‚Äôt want it to be ‚Äúnormal‚Äù, i don‚Äôt want to get used to it. i want to still be chocked to hear about igm or i want to have to read 5x an article to get my head around the fact that there was a shooting... you know what i mean or am i weird thinking this ? does this make sense ? #protectintersexkids #intersexrights #toocutetobebinary #bodilyautonomy #myintersexbody #intersexpride #humanrights

text:
vulnerability #fsn223
in class we were told to post each week about the topic discussed and our thoughts on it. ‚Ä¢
2018 was the beginning of standing up and accepting myself. the movement #metoo allowed me to be vulnerable and express the abuse i received as a child. of course i also had to come out of the closet cause it was 20gayteen after all. being open about my queer identity was a massive step that i‚Äôm still adjusting to. the environment i grew up in was not supportive. i still deal with feelings of shame because of the way the queer community was talked about growing up and still is. my hope in 2019 is to be as open as i can about continuing to grow my understanding of my identity and improving my mental health. bringing vulnerability into my work is essential. in the fashion industry being vulnerable is a key component to making change, creating unique designs and understanding others. you have to be vulnerable to make a real difference.

text:
"ÔΩÇÔΩåÔΩÅÔΩìÔΩêÔΩàÔΩÖÔΩçÔΩèÔΩïÔΩì„ÄÄ
ÔΩÇÔΩÖÔΩåÔΩèÔΩñÔΩÖÔΩÑ" (2)
he took me away from everything else and then he took 'all of me'. he was all i was left with and yet, i never owned him as he left me with nothing to call mine.
i knew not what my fault was. i know not what my fault is. i trusted and i broke.
2 months back, i moved in with him. he promised me a forever. i could see it in his eyes. he said he'd never leave me alone.
¬†but he's gone. gone for someone else.
i begged him to want me but he didn't want to. he was with me just for himself.
.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
"the hand is a unique and powerful expression - 'i am here, this is me, i matter'. i used black ink and kept the piece minimal to enhance this message." this is the first of two #artforgaia entries from @hannahhobbsartist a survivor who lives in dorset. thank you hannah, for sharing your inspiration with us. what a powerful voice for justice. she says: "both my entries are about identity, which is a concept which i personally and many survivors have battled with and continue to battle with. personally, being a victim of csa robbed me of my identity; i lost who i was and to this day i struggle to know who i am. 
it is a very deep feeling of loss and requires a lot of processing and grief work to learn to live with it. i also believe it is a human right/need to have ones own unique identity, and it is beyond cruel for someone to take that away from anyone, let alone innocent children and teenagers."
#justiceforgaia #justiceforallofus #itsnotok #itsnotok2019 #survivorsunite #survivor #survivorart #endvawg #vawg #metoo #hearmetoo #metoomovement #ptsdkills #mentalhealth #mentalhealthmatters #mentalhealthawareness #dorset #crisisinrapecrisis #supportnotsuspicion

text:
what is your relationship to beauty? does the word feel like a measure of societally-imposed worth, carved atop the surface of your skin? or do you know beauty bone-deep as something untouchable, divinity shining outwards from your very depths? üíö reflections. i‚Äôm honoured to be hosting an evening of body love, blindfolded movement & women‚Äôs circle this friday with my soul sister @tania.hart to dive into this subject.
‚Ä¢
in today‚Äôs profit-motivated culture, we are bombarded with up to 5000 ads per day that work to convince us of our unworthiness. with the global cosmetic/weight loss industry making over 650 billion dollars a year, companies attempt to blind us to the beauty that is our naturalness, literally profiting off of low self-esteem. this is a robbery of our time, money, and most importantly, the knowing of worth that is our birthright. 
because of this, the word beauty has become completely distorted. 
we‚Äôve been taught to see beauty as something surface-level, external, and exclusive. 
with tender hearts, we have felt into the devastating impacts of this wound and feel how essential it is for us women to come together and reclaim our innate beauty as an embodied knowing ‚ú®‚ú®‚ú®this is why we have created this 
workshop featuring ‚ú® opening circle: reflecting on the idea and societal definitions of beauty vs. internal experiences ‚ú® blindfolded movement: a journey back into the body using intuitive movement & dance. re-meet beauty as a feeling, not a measure ‚ú®self-love journey & partnerwork: reconnecting with sight as we remove our blindfolds, self-appreciate and honour. ‚ú® closing circle: sharing circle and solidarity in reflection. integration tools for translating this felt experience of beauty into every mirror and moment üôè reclamation for all relations. space is limited. dm for details to reserve your spot ‚ö†Ô∏è photography by @womynwithheart

text:
surviving r. kelly in cultures of enablement

by keyvan shafiei

an expos√© typically indicts the character of its subject; ‚Äúsurviving r. kelly‚Äù indicts a public that knew of his character and did nothing about it, a public that constructed an elaborate architecture of denial and has chosen to live in it.¬†‚Äî¬†jelani cobb,¬†new yorker, january 2019

how did kelly get away with his misdeeds for so long? how did mainstream culture tolerate this, not to mention outright encourage and lionize it at times? and isn‚Äôt mainstream culture, at least in some ways,¬†ourculture? if so, then are¬†we¬†notresponsible for having egged on kelly‚Äôs celebrity and status, behind whose thickly-constructed shield he was able to carry out his egregious acts?
yes, is the obvious answer here. we are accountable. at this juncture in the era of #metoo, the story of r. kelly is in many ways familiar to us. broadly, it is the story of harvey weinstein, bill cosby, kevin spacey, and louis c.k., among others. it is the story of open secrets, failures of allyship, and culturally manufactured disbelief and ignorance. simply put, it is the painful tale of wrongdoers hiding in plain sight and evading accountability, because they inhabit what i call¬†cultures of enablement, wherein¬†our¬†everyday actions implicate us in gross, systemic injustices. before i unpack this claim, however, i should first explain what i think a ‚Äòculture‚Äô is and consists of. i find particularly helpful here an account that¬†sally haslanger¬†has recently put forth.

https://blog.apaonline.org/2019/02/04/surviving-r-kelly-in-cultures-of-enablement/

behind these blue eyes there is a story yet to be told. a past that haunts me even to this day. a deep scar that grew from infancy and kept growing deeper through the years. something that has affected every part of my life leading to posttraumatic stress disorder and paralysing nightmares. i have made it my mission in life to get justice. this person has been working with children for the last 20 years even after i finally was brave enough to tell my supportive parents and the police my story when i was 9 and still to this day continues in a job surrounded by children. i have been working on this case for years now and it saddens me that even though the police have received so much information of other victims and withnesses, they still do nothing. i can no longer carry this weight on my shoulders alone. it is time for to speak out - and not suffer in silence!  i encourage anyone who has been affected by sexual abuse to speak out and go to the police no matter how "small" of an incident. only then can we have justice, prevent lives to be ruined and finally be set free. behind this smile there is a sad story but i am a fighter and i know you are too. #metoo #metoomovement #childabusesurvivor #ptsdawareness #canaryislands #teacher #kripos #norskskolegrandcanaria #colegionoruego #politiet #dontsufferinsilence #childrenofabuse #ptsdrecovery #suicideprevention #kanari√∏yene #grancanaria @reddbarna @nettpatruljen @overgrepphistorier @forebyggovergrepp

text:
men, what role are you choosing to play today?

are you pretending to play strong when you feel weak, confident when you feel insecure, or happy when you feel sad.

i‚Äôm tired of this role that is being communicated to boys and girls all over the world that boys are masculine and women are feminine. we are both, but when we lean into that feminine side what becomes the consequence? in a man‚Äôs mind voices say we are going to be shamed. what if today we want to be vulnerable and want help with the tears we are battling. what if we want to talk about how crappy life is and want support from other men. how do we do this? where do we go to find like minded men? what does this look like?

men, i can say taking this journey of healing was a risk i wasn‚Äôt willing to pass on. the amount of shit i had running in my head was atrocious. it feels amazing to tell people i love my life vs the old thoughts i hid from everyone. it was loud!! the one that kept saying, i don‚Äôt want to wake up tomorrow, i just want to die in my sleep.

but, there was a voice even louder that kept saying i love myself. i don‚Äôt want to feel this pain anymore, i want an amazing life and i want to be free of all the limitations i‚Äôve placed on myself.

the healing starts with recognizing we aren‚Äôt indestructible and we do need help. the bell lets talk doesn‚Äôt end on the day it‚Äôs started. men and women let‚Äôs keep talking!! there‚Äôs no end to men‚Äôs mental health.

text:
more often than not in the doctor's office consent is assumed and not asked for, especially for women, and especially when it comes to gynecologists.
it's often just assumed by doctors that women will consent to invasive exams and they don't even feel the need to ask if their patients are actually ok with the exam or give them the opportunity to refuse. it's gotten so bad that a surprising number of women don't even know that they can refuse exams such as pap smears and pelvic exams when they don't want them. many little girls grow up believing that intrusive gynecological exams are mandatory, some adult women don't even know they have the right to say no.
and worst of all, doctors everywhere are enabling this toxic idea that consent somehow ceases to matter in the doctor's office with things like mandatory pelvic exams to get safe and efficient birth control.
consent always matters.
be it a doctor, your husband, your boyfriend, or a stranger on the street consent should always be asked for and never assumed.
#consent #endsexualviolence #wedeservebetter #metoo #birthcontrol #smeartest #papsmear #feminism #feminist #womenshealth #womenempowerment #womensrights

text:
mental health is an invisible illness. you can't see how it effects me mentally. you cant see the thoughts that go through my head related to ptsd or depression. or know when i'm smiling cause i'm happy or when i'm smiling because i don't want to be judged.
people fail to understand that we can't always see or tell what's going on in someone's life. we don't know everyone's story. just because we can't see what's wrong doesn't mean it's not real.
.
.

text:
i would like to ask everyone to please click on the link in my bio for my little girl. 
a boy in her classroom touched her in a sexually inappropriate way and the school administration refuses to do anything about it! my daughter feels very violated and she can't concentrate with her abuser sitting 2 seats away from her! 
when i asked the principal of the school to have the boy change classrooms, he stated "that's not necessary and we spoke to him. everything is fine." my wife and i are outraged at the way the school has handled this situation and now my daughter has missed 10 days of school because she won't sit next to her abuser! 
my family and i are asking you to please sign this petition and share this post so my daughter can return to class without reliving her attack over and over again. 
thank you ‚ù§

dr. b & family
.
.

text:
.
training someone to change will work, for a while but to have lasting change a deeper shift must take place.
consider the #metoo movement and the need for a change in the behaviors and mindsets of some men.
.
i walk with the realization that i carry both masculine and feminine natures. i not only know this but i allow them to be activated in a unified balanced way. 
this has allowed me more insight and understanding with women and men. a very good quality to possess.
.
note: for men carrying their feminine nature, this is not the same as being effeminate. many will automatically think they are one in the same but they are not.
.
when i am in my duality of these natures my behavior, attitude and mindset are now resonating much differently than if i simply walked solely in my masculinity.
.
this is where i believe the problem truly lay.
what compounds the problem is when a man only walks in his  physical being because he hasn't done the work of understanding his spiritual, emotional, mental and sexual parts that complete him.
.
i am so passionate to help men discover parts of themselves they never knew existed. emerging as new men and showing sides of themselves to the woman in their lives that she never experienced before.
.
this is the shift that needs to take place and that will change everything.
.
.
.
.

text:
‚Äôi was a victim too‚Äô ‚Äì uche jombo speaks on sexual assault in nollywood
.
.
the 39-year-old actress, screen writer & producer, made this disclosure in an interview with hiptv while speaking on the widespread allegations of sexual assault on upcoming actresses. ‚Äúi‚Äôve been in that kind of situation twice during my starting days,‚Äù she said. ‚Äúi rehearsed for almost two weeks only to come next and find that someone else was reading my role because i declined the request to ‚Äòsee me‚Äô (for sex). ‚Äúi wept seriously, i was hurt but four to five years later, i made it big.‚Äù explaining how she survived and maintained her stance at the time, jombo said: ‚Äúit is personal integrity. in my days, we move on when we‚Äôre denied opportunities for refusing to give in to sexual demands. ‚Äúsometimes, it‚Äôs your individual strength, drive and process that matters. what takes some six months to accomplish might take others six years. ‚Äúare you ready to wait for your time or you just want a shortcut that leads to no long-lasting opportunity? if you want the shortcut, chances are that there are people willing to give it.‚Äù jombo said people who engage in such acts should be called out explaining that this would force nollywood recruiters and opportunity givers who indulge in such acts to ‚Äúbe humans again‚Äù. .
.

text:
a hard question that needs to be asked:

hetero ladies: do you care about consent and want the men in your life to always respect your boundaries? and: do you also find it unsexy if a man asks if he can kiss you? if you answered yes to both questions, you're being hypocritical, and a part of the problem. i hesitate to use such strong language, but it's simply true. men are under two very strong and very contradictory pressures in society today: on one hand, to be good feminists who care about #metoo, and on the other hand, to hold up the stereotypical manly role of initiating physical contact without "ruining the moment." this is a literally impossible position to be in. can you imagine the confusion and pressure? 
the thing about gender relations and norms is that women can be part of the problem, too. we can reinforce harmful behaviors and stereotypes, too. if we want to reform gender relations for the better, then it's our obligation not just to analyze, critique, and reform others, but also ourselves. contrary to what many women tell me, it is not impossible to change what you're into. it really isn't. it just takes introspection. it takes deconstructing your biases. it takes looking at things you had previously ignored because society told you to (e.g., gentle men, communicative men) in a new, appreciative light. and maybe you don't want to change what you're into, but that requires honesty with yourself and others and communication, too. in today's world it is only fair that we make it clear what we want from and with the men in our life. so shall we do some digging and get to work? üîßüîßüîß #consentculture #metoo #feminism #genderrelations #whatwomenwant #unpopularopinion

why are #metoo accused getting a pass in kidlit? üìöaccusations against @drewdaywalt: ‚Äúanother writer says, ‚Äúduring an award ceremony during a conference in los angeles, i thought how lucky i was to sit next to a huge bestseller in the children‚Äôs industry. our entire table enjoyed dinner together and near the end he expressed how he‚Äôd be interested in reading my work and give feedback. as a newer writer, this was a dream and we exchanged cards. after that, i started to receive messages from him about how beautiful my social media pictures were and that we should get together sometime. he then proceeded to tell me that his wife was fine with it, as she dates other people too. when i told him i was married and declined, he then got upset and pretended to never have met me.‚Äù for this writer, ‚Äúhe made me never want to go back to los angeles. this happened years ago, and he made me feel like an object, not a professional.‚Äù üìö accusation 1: ‚Äúmy story was also mentioned in anne‚Äôs article, and drew daywalt was the one that made me never want to return to los angeles. this is really tough for me to post, even anonymously, because i‚Äôve always tried to be such a peacemaker, but honestly, the more i thought about it, the more i realized that this goes beyond me. i felt confused and hurt over the entire interaction for a long while, and after reading anne‚Äôs response in her article, she truly helped me understand why i felt the way i did. thank you, anne! and to those also speaking up, i‚Äôm glad we‚Äôre all having this conversation, and my hope is that those being called out will truly reach out for help and want to change. ‚Äù

accusation 2 (via twitter dm to me): ‚Äúhello, i was recently told about your blog post featuring comments about men in the kid lit community who are accused of sexually harassing women. when i read anne ursu‚Äôs article, i knew exactly who one of the men were. drew daywalt. he used the same lines with me and more. i am forever traumatized by that man. i wish to remain anonymous.‚Äù üìömy post here: https://www.pragmaticmom.com/2019/01/why-are-metoo-accused-getting-a-pass-in-kidlit/ #drewdaywalt #sexualmisconduct #picturebook #thedaythecrayonsquit

inspired by #tedtalk of #taranaburke 
the talk is mind boggling, deeply disturbing and highly thought provoking. 
we seem to oversee feelings of numbness, generally avoiding them and looking the other way, like if we don't see them, they will stop to exist. but it doesn't happen that way. this accumulation of feelings is bound to raise it's neck someday or the other, if an act of closure, reconciliation or forgiveness is not done. and until then, forcing ourselves to not feel numb, is the only option one has.
.
.

text:
"he's a good man"....
many victims have heard this statement made about their abuser when they disclose their abuse to their family. it's almost as if the family is asking the victim to reframe their opinion of their abuser through the lens of how the family is choosing to see the abuser. or, they are somehow trying to excuse the abuser's behavior or absolve the abuser of their crime. however, if you've been the victim of sexual abuse and this is what you were told about your abuser, it's a lie. anyone who sexually abuses a child is not a good man! a good man does not molest children. a good man does not cause lifelong trauma or inflict physical, mental and/or emotional pain on a child. a good man does not seek self gratification over the wellbeing of a child. do not allow your family to convince you that you have to separate a person's carefully constructed public persona from their private behavior. 
do not allow your family's warped sense of loyalty to your abuser make you feel as though you need to view this man as anything other than the monster that you know them to be. do not allow your family to silence, shame or guilt you into reframing your opinion of someone who has violated you in this way. stand in your truth. expose them. we are standing with you, we believe you, and we know that he is not a good man. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #super bowl

text:
hey all! wecan is accepting artwork for the @raperecoverycenter 's sexual assault awareness month event in april. we're accepting line work and combining the selected images to make a mural/ large canvases that the community can paint and add to during the event. our theme this year is reclaiming a love for your body after trauma. as a guideline for the pieces, we'd love to represent self love for all survivors and all bodies. feel free to share this with anyone who may be interested.

we did a similar project in 2017 and love how it turned out- swipe to see one of the completed canvases! thank you to everyone who made it possible! feel free to dm me if you are interested in submitting art work this year- we're accepting submissions until monday, february 25th at 9pm.
.
.
.
.
#supportwomen #supportsurvivors #linework #wecanslc #saltlakeartist #utahartist #callforartists #illustration #drawing #healing #loveyourbody #selflove #healingthroughart #saam #metoo #wehealtogether

hey all! wecan is accepting artwork for the @raperecoverycenter 's sexual assault awareness month event in april. we're accepting line work and combining the selected images to make a mural/ large canvases that the community can paint and add to during the event. our theme this year is reclaiming a love for your body after trauma. as a guideline for the pieces, we'd love to represent self love for all survivors and all bodies. feel free to share this with anyone who may be interested.

we did a similar project in 2017 and love how it turned out- swipe to see one of the completed canvases! thank you to everyone who made it possible! feel free to dm me if you are interested in submitting art work this year- we're accepting submissions until monday, february 25th at 9pm.
.

.

text:
collage of misery - as a victim and a survivor of rape, sexual violence, child abuse, traumatic childhood, suicide attempt, authoritative violence, gross objectification and racial violence, it takes a lot of energy to just get out of bed and accomplish basic day-to-day tasks. there isn't a day i've not thought of suicide. i don't know what happiness is. i don't know what love is. i know what betrayal is, i know what pain is, i know what misery is,  i know what anguish is, i know what despair is... as qpoc and queer refugees, we're exposed to extreme forms of violence and the privileged are oblivious to our sufferings or refuse to acknowledge our struggles. we're treated as third-class citizens and without human decency. all our past pain, the pain we face everyday and the paranoid expectations of violence, make our lives a living hell. but, we're fodder to the privileged monsters jokes and ridicules, our pain and tragedies are scrutinized and judged, we're deemed as animals and criminals. 
here's a thought. we've enough pain to deal with, so leave us the f*ck alone and let us heal.

here's a thought. we've enough pain to deal with, so leave us the f*ck alone and let us heal.

text:
@genielashorty genie pimentel and i are super excited to be organizing together #nyccelebrateswomen #brunch #fundraiser let‚Äôs continue the conversation about #metoo in the latina community. #savethedate there will be a panel, raffle and many wonderful surprises. the concept of this year‚Äôs art is women mural in #nyc. the art on this flyer is by puerto rican artist @yasminhernandezart 
this mural honors the common histories and struggles of mexicans and puerto ricans and is a call for continued and increased solidarity between the two communities. visually, the concept is inspired by frida kahlo‚Äôs painting, ‚Äúlas dos fridas.‚Äù in my design for ‚Äúsoldaderas‚Äù however, frida kahlo sits holding the hand of the equally fierce puerto rican poet, julia de burgos. the image was partly informed by my work as an artist educator at el museo del barrio in new york city (2002-2009). while there, i worked with various kahlo pieces as well as casasola's photo archive documenting the mexican revolution, including images of soldaderas-women soldiers of the revolution. though i had the idea for this mural since around 2005, it was not until the spring of 2011, through a collaboration between art for change, hope community, inc and el barrio arts cluster that the project was finally able to get off the ground. i began working on ‚Äúsoldaderas‚Äù on friday, june 3rd, 2011 at the modesto flores community garden on lexington avenue between 104th and 105th streets and unveiled it on july 6 of that year.
name: Nathalie Tejada

this mural honors the common histories and struggles of mexicans and pueo ricans and is a call for continued and increased solidarity between the two communities. visually, the concept is inspired by frida kahlo‚Äôs painting, ‚Äúlas dos fridas.‚Äù in my design for ‚Äúsoldaderas‚Äù however, frida kahlo sits holding the hand of the equally fierce pueo rican poet, julia de burgos. the image was paly informed by my work as an aist educator at el museo del barrio in new york city (2002-2009). while there, i worked with various kahlo pieces as well as casasola's photo archive documenting the mexican revolution, including images of soldaderas-women soldiers of the revolution. though i had the idea for this mural since around 2005, it was not until the spring of 2011, through a collaboration between a for change, hope community, inc and el barrio as cluster that the project was finally able to get off the ground. i began working on ‚Äúsoldaderas‚Äù on friday, june 3rd, 2011 at the modesto flores community garden on lexington avenue between 104th and 105th streets and unveiled it on july 6 of that year.

.

.
.

text_retweet:
wanderlust

repost from @noji.reads: at the #philippinereadersandwritersfestival last year, i got a signed copy of #manilawasalongtimeago and metaphorically, it came with a passport.

the author whisked me away to the places i've never been to (except manila) yet seemed familiar from the settings of some of the stories i've read -- quebec, berlin, new york, paris, the vatican, san francisco, athens, milan, amsterdam, √§hus, budapest, singapore, phuket, prague, and venice.

its stories are atmospheric and richly told through varied forms, genre, and treatment.

one of the stories is pan de regla whose excerpt i've read in the philippine panorama before the book was published. it's nice to read the story in full. it's a familiar narrative of the #metoo era with its tale of lifelong trauma.

the inspiring preface of this book also struck me, aplenty of musings and wisdom about writing and life.

#thankyouforreading #stories #shortstories #writersofinstagram #aastories #mybooksjourney3 #fiction #museumofnaturalhistory #manila #philippines #mytravelingbooks

text_retweet:
reposted from @muslimahnewsid - / perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada¬†umbrella act¬†lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan¬†#metoo¬†yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, ‚Äúpertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‚Äòamanah‚Äô¬†beijing platform for action¬†(bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‚Äòkontrol seksual‚Äô itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.‚Äù
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi¬†qawwam¬†(pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
‚Äúmenjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,‚Äù ungkapnya kepada¬†mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
‚Äî‚Äî
follow @muslimahnewsid
.

#khilafahajaranislam 
#selamatkanperempuan

#islamsolusinegeri

stop_filter_tweet: reposted - / perempuan butuh syariat islam , bukan ruu pks / . pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan , pratama julia sunjandari , menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang ( ruu ) penghapusan kekerasan seksual ( pks ) sungguh mengada-ada . . pasalnya , menurut pratma , bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai . perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual . . pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks , ‚Äú peama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal . muatan srhr ( sexual reproductive healths rights ) sebagai ‚Äò amanah ‚Äô beijing platform action ( bpfa ) amat kuat . frasa ‚Äò kontrol seksual ‚Äô itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur . termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun. ‚Äù . kedua , kata pratma julia , merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri . tak ada lagi qawwam ( pemimpin ) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat . ketiga , menikam syariat islam . kalangan liberal , dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah . . ‚Äú menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata , ‚Äù ungkapnya kepada mnews , rabu ( 30/1/2019 ) . . . ‚Äî‚Äî follow uslimahnewsid . elamatkanperempuan

born and raised in the bronx, ny,  tarana burke is a black civil rights activist who was the original founder of the "me too" movement, which she started in 2006. it later became a global phenomenon that raised awareness about sexual harassment, abuse, and assault in society in 2017.  burke  and other influential female activists were named "the silence breakers" by time magazine in 2017. she currently serves as senior director at girls for gender equity in brooklyn, ny. we should all be more like tarana burke. 
#taranaburke #metoo  #blackhistorymonth #everymonthshouldbeblackhistorymonth

text:
‚ú®s p r e a d  y o u r  w i n g s‚ú®
before we had to #muterkelly "i believe i can fly" was my go to song for every transition i was going through, and back in the days the lyrics would have been a perfect caption to this picture. however as someone who has managed to escape from an abusive relationship, graciously turning my back on r kelly's tainted legacy was easy. there are so many uplifting songs out there anyway.
.
as illogical as it may sound, it's never easy to leave a toxic relationship. toxic or limiting environments, whether in your personal or professional life have a way to impact your confidence and to make you believe you are not good enough to aim higher and wish better. i even remember someone telling me confidently that "it's better to deal with a devil that you know, than with an angel you don't know". i personally believe is better to invest in yourself and develop the skills, the self awareness, the financial & emotional independence you need to be your own hero if necessary. unfortunately without the proper support system (friends, mentors, inspiration, education) it's easy to get stuck in a situation that does not serve our higher purpose.
.
‚ú®t h i s  i s  w h y  i  d o w h a t  i  d o‚ú®
after growing from a vulnerable young woman to a sought-after professional in my fields of interest, i now coach ambitious women willing to overcome the limitations in their lives to build the career or business they were made for.
.
join me next thursday 7.30 pm gmt for an instagram live session on @businessrulesforwomen page. i will tell you more about the strategy i used to create my own career fairy tale and how you could too! 
1. follow me on instagram 
2. follow @businessrulesforwomen
3. mark your calendar for thursday 7.30 pm gmt ( 8.30 pm lagos douala & paris time,  10.30 pm nairobi time)
4. tag your friends who may want to join the live session
5. share any question you would like me to tackle in the comments!
see you on thursday to make the magic happen!‚ú®√¨

text: some of these were taken months, even days before my assault. for months after being sexually assaulted, i remember looking at photos like these & crying because i was grieving the woman i once was. it‚Äôs been almost a year & a half since my attack and everyday since the night of september 30, 2017 it hasn‚Äôt left my mind. yesterday, my perpetrator plead guilty & i was finally able to breathe again knowing he could never hurt anyone the way he has hurt me. in sharing a piece of my story, i hope to spread awareness & speak the truth i fight for everyday. god has truly blessed me with unbelievable strength & support. i am forever grateful. survivors, i am here. you are strong, you are loved, you are not alone & it is not your fault!! #metoo #stoprape #nomeansno #supportsurvivors
